&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Item #:&lt;/strong&gt; SCP-5547&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Clearance:&lt;/strong&gt; 3&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;container-class:&lt;/strong&gt; euclid&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;disruption-class:&lt;/strong&gt; ekhi&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;risk-class:&lt;/strong&gt; notice&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;threat level:&lt;/strong&gt; red&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Special Containment Procedures:&lt;/strong&gt; SCP-5547-1, SCP-5547-2, and SCP-5547-3 are held in a 10x10x5 meter containment cell connect to 2 (two) standard humanoid containment chambers. Should any instance of SCP-5547 misbehave, threaten SCP-5547-1 with thermal weaponry until they stop. When a discussion event occurs attempts to convince them to bring things back with them or take things can be done with the approval of an O5, such attempts are to stop if SCP-5547-3 claims &amp;quot;They won&#039;t like that&amp;quot;. SCP-5547-1 and 2 are to hand over any item it brings back but may request them for future narrative events. After a narrative event a d-class is to be sent in to retrieve the SCP-5547-4 instance, which will then be added to the site breakroom. Should a death event occur SCP-5547-2 is to be transferred to a 5x5x5 meter secondary containment chamber filled with water for one hour with in five (5) minutes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Description:&lt;/strong&gt; SCP-5547-1 is a red type capable of altering it&#039;s biology to a high degree showing the ability to replicate traits of several anomalous lifeforms. It primarily takes the form of an underweight Caucasian male teenager and in this form displays sapience and sentience. SCP-5547-1 displays extreme thermophobia do to thermal weaponry causing several death events. Death events are the events that occur when SCP-5547-1 dies. Five minutes after it&#039;s death a gaseous substance will fly out of SCP-5547-2 and start releasing a unknown amount of energy for approximately 40 minutes resulting in an instance of SCP-5547-1 with all memories of the previous instance. During discussion events they spend most of their time listening, making simple suggestions to SCP-5547-3. During narrative events they have shown anomalous knowledge, however they have not been confirmed to use this knowledge outside of them. SCP-5547-1 is generally friendly and talkative, often talking to SCP-5547-2 or asking SCP-5547-3 for snacks and to help in clean the containment chamber.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;SCP-5547-2 is a light blue crystal ball with a radius of 30&amp;#160;cm and a mass of 50 kilograms that constantly produces EVE, SCP-5547-2 is at least as intelligent as an adolescent human but do to it&#039;s aggressive behaviour this can&#039;t be can&#039;t test further. SCP-5547-2 is made of a substance that is indestructible, non conductive, and completely unreactive. SCP-5547-2 can manifest SCP-5547-2A which is theorized to be made of the same substance as SCP-5547-2 within 10 meters of it and stay in the same position relative to it. It can move SCP-5547-2A with it&#039;s thoughts however the substance will disappear if farther than 10 meters from SCP-5547-2 and can&#039;t directly interact with SCP-5547-2. It uses SCP-5547-2A to attack anyone near it other than SCP-5547-1 or 3. During discussion events it is very critical while offering little advice. The object is sarcastic, and openly hostile towards everyone except SCP-5547-1. In narrative events it shown high levels of thaumatology capabilities in SCP-5547-1&#039;s possession.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;SCP-5547-3 is a underweight Caucasian male teenager with the ability to alter reality with a method unknown to the foundation to an unknown degree. During discussion events it will usually suggest a human or humanoid with knowledge of the anomalous, and two anomalies which it comes up with ideas for stories including them and SCP-5547-1 and 2. During narrative events he stays in the real world and handles the side effects of narrative events, only appearing in narratives if something goes wrong in it.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Discussion events normally occur a week before a narrative event, however they have also lead to the disappearance, changes, destruction, and appearance of anomalies and people with knowledge of the anomalous. SCP-5547-3 always starts the conversation, SCP-5547-1 listens quietly to him, and SCP-5547-2 points out lack of originality, inconsistencies and missing information. For an example of a discussion event see addendum 1.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Narrative events consists of the disappearance of SCP-5547-1 and 2, the humanoid mentioned, and depending on unknown variables instances of the anomalies mentioned. SCP-5547-3 will then use it&#039;s reality altering abilities to act in place of the humanoid, and depending on the anomaly act in it&#039;s place, explain to those associated with the anomaly it is safe, or nothing. After a time varying from 5 minutes to 6 months SCP-5547-1 and 2 return in the containment cell, unless a death event occurs in during the narrative event then only SCP-5547-2 returns. The Humanoid returns as it was either before or at the end of the narrative sapience beings claim they got to choose, however they keep memory of the event either way, if the humanoid is not sapience it is always returned to how it was before the event with no memory of it reappearing where SCP-5547-3 claims they belong. Anomalies that are not in SCP-5547-1 or 2&#039;s possession or destroy return to where SCP-5547-3 claims they belong, anomalies destroyed don&#039;t reappear, anomalies in SCP-5547-1 or 2&#039;s possession at the end of the evw return in SCP-5547-1 or 2&#039;s possession. On the desk in one of the standard humanoid containment chamber connected their containment chamber SCP-5547-4 will appear. SCP-5547-4 are books written in English about the items that disappeared in the narrative event that caused it. SCP-5547-4 instances have no anomalous properties other than their origin. For an example of a narrative event see addendum 2.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Addendum 1:&lt;/strong&gt; This discussion event was not recorded, however all attempts to delete it results in SCP-5547-3 appearing next to the one editing it, slapping them and disappearing with the section restored.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;blockquote&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;SCP-5547-3:&lt;/strong&gt; Do you think they figured it out yet.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;SCP-5547-2:&lt;/strong&gt; Ok, first of all you made this so that any level 3 can read this despite S Andrew Swann&#039;s Proposal being restricted to one O5&#039;s knowledge, so this is going to get deleted.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;SCP-5547-1:&lt;/strong&gt; This is Arthur Eryur&#039;s canon he can do what ever he wants with that article and besides several canons have a Pataphysics department which would require such knowledge. To go even farther he agreed to make it so others in verse don&#039;t see the first 9 lines.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Arthur&lt;/strong&gt; Thanks for using my real at least in canon name.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;SCP-5547-2:&lt;/strong&gt; You need to clarify you are SCP-5547-3 so they don&#039;t think you are a fourth entity Arthur.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Arthur:&lt;/strong&gt; Well you just did for me, Arc.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Arc:&lt;/strong&gt; You suck, anyway now that you made us an article are we going to do the discussion event you promised?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Arthur:&lt;/strong&gt; Yes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;SCP-5547-1:&lt;/strong&gt; Since this is the last chance I have to say it, my name is Walter.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;SCP-5547-3:&lt;/strong&gt; I say we bring back &lt;a class=&quot;newpage&quot; href=&quot;http://www.scpwiki.com/scp-547-d&quot;&gt;SCP-547-D&lt;/a&gt; who died after his heart was shattered by a bullet despite it being made of plasma and it previously vaporizing everything that touched it.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;SCP-5547-2:&lt;/strong&gt; That makes no sense but it was done by Dr. Clef so I guess it is possible. But you want to have a guy whose anomalous trait let&#039;s him control something that gave 1&lt;sup class=&quot;footnoteref&quot;&gt;&lt;a id=&quot;footnoteref-881717-1&quot; href=&quot;javascript:;&quot; class=&quot;footnoteref&quot;  &gt;1&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/sup&gt; trauma, dumbass.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;SCP-5547-3:&lt;/strong&gt; I am also giving him the powers &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.scpwiki.com/scp-732&quot;&gt;SCP-732&lt;/a&gt; claimed he had, orb&lt;sup class=&quot;footnoteref&quot;&gt;&lt;a id=&quot;footnoteref-881717-2&quot; href=&quot;javascript:;&quot; class=&quot;footnoteref&quot;  &gt;2&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/sup&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;SCP-5547-2:&lt;/strong&gt; You are not helping your case. 1 you going to be okay with it.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;SCP-5547-1:&lt;/strong&gt; Yes, Arc&lt;sup class=&quot;footnoteref&quot;&gt;&lt;a id=&quot;footnoteref-881717-3&quot; href=&quot;javascript:;&quot; class=&quot;footnoteref&quot;  &gt;3&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/sup&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;SCP-5547-3:&lt;/strong&gt; We will be using &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.scpwiki.com/scp-4127&quot;&gt;SCP-4127&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.scpwiki.com/scp-5720&quot;&gt;SCP-5720&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;SCP-5547-2:&lt;/strong&gt; the heads or tails one.&lt;sup class=&quot;footnoteref&quot;&gt;&lt;a id=&quot;footnoteref-881717-4&quot; href=&quot;javascript:;&quot; class=&quot;footnoteref&quot;  &gt;4&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/sup&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;SCP-5547-3:&lt;/strong&gt; The tails one.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;SCP-5547-2:&lt;/strong&gt; Maybe we shouldn&#039;t have an anomaly that defines the future, dumbass.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;SCP-5547-3:&lt;/strong&gt; I suppose, Walter any ideas.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;SCP-5547-1:&lt;/strong&gt; Let&#039;s see &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.scpwiki.com/scp-4051&quot;&gt;Rainer&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.scpwiki.com/scp-4494&quot;&gt;The Spector&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a class=&quot;newpage&quot; href=&quot;http://www.scpwiki.com/scp4640&quot;&gt;SCP4640&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.scpwiki.com/scp-4128&quot;&gt;SCP-4128&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.scpwiki.com/scp-4131&quot;&gt;SCP-4131&lt;/a&gt; would all make lovely parallels to Coldplay.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;SCP-5547-2:&lt;/strong&gt; I get all of those except SCP-4131.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;SCP-5547-3:&lt;/strong&gt; I mean they can technically be considered a super hero.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;SCP-5547-2:&lt;/strong&gt; Got me there, dumbass.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;SCP-5547-3:&lt;/strong&gt; SCP-4051 seems the best choice.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;(do to the potential danger SCP-4051 Interacting with an instance of SCP-5547 Dr. Smith was sent in to suggest a different anomaly, specifically Olympia for the purpose of testing their usefulness if reactived, Smith was told to leverage SCP-5547-1&#039;s crush on Olympia.)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Dr. Smith:&lt;/strong&gt; May I suggest a different option?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;SCP-5547-3:&lt;/strong&gt; I don&#039;t see why not.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Dr. Smith:&lt;/strong&gt; Olympia.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;SCP-5547-1:&lt;/strong&gt; This is a much better idea.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;SCP-5547-2:&lt;/strong&gt; I am ok with it.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;SCP-5547-3:&lt;/strong&gt; I guess I don&#039;t have a choice sure.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;SCP-5547-2:&lt;/strong&gt; You want to do a thing with two dead people, I suggest &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.scpwiki.com/scp-1230&quot;&gt;book keeper&lt;/a&gt; over that crane you are obsessed with.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;SCP-5547-1:&lt;/strong&gt; They have a point, plus that would let him know how to use the powers you are giving him.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;SCP-5547-3:&lt;/strong&gt; Fine.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;SCP-5547-2:&lt;/strong&gt; So, what is the narrative, dumbass.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;SCP-5547-3:&lt;/strong&gt; I have no idea!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;lt;End of discussion event&amp;gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Addendum 2:&lt;/strong&gt; [Data Error]&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;footnotes-footer&quot;&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;title&quot;&gt;Footnotes&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;footnote-footer&quot; id=&quot;footnote-881717-1&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;javascript:;&quot;  &gt;1&lt;/a&gt;. SCP-5547-2 refers to SCP-5547-1 as 1, itself as 2 and SCP-5547-3 as dumbass.&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;footnote-footer&quot; id=&quot;footnote-881717-2&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;javascript:;&quot;  &gt;2&lt;/a&gt;. SCP-5547-3 refers to SCP-5547-1 as Walter, SCP-5547-2 as orb, and itself as Arthur.&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;footnote-footer&quot; id=&quot;footnote-881717-3&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;javascript:;&quot;  &gt;3&lt;/a&gt;. SCP-5547-1 refers to themself as red, SCP-5547-2 as Arc, and SCP-5547-3 as boss.&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;footnote-footer&quot; id=&quot;footnote-881717-4&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;javascript:;&quot;  &gt;4&lt;/a&gt;. it is not currently known what SCP-XXXX-2 is referring to by this.&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;footer-wikiwalk-nav&quot;&gt;
&lt;div style=&quot;text-align: center;&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;#171; &lt;a class=&quot;newpage&quot; href=&quot;http://www.scpwiki.com/scp-5546&quot;&gt;SCP-5546&lt;/a&gt; | SCP-5547 | &lt;a class=&quot;newpage&quot; href=&quot;http://www.scpwiki.com/scp-5548&quot;&gt;SCP-5548&lt;/a&gt; &amp;#187;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;[div class=&amp;quot;blockquote&amp;quot;]&lt;br /&gt;
Apologies for the lack of a narrative event I just can&#039;t take the final step yet.&lt;br /&gt;
[/div&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Just kidding&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Anomalies effected:&lt;/strong&gt; SCP-547-D, Olympia, SCP-1230-1&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Lasted for:&lt;/strong&gt; 1 day&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;SCP-5547-3 Behavior changes:&lt;/strong&gt; none&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;SCP-5547-4 instance:&lt;/strong&gt; see below&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;blockquote&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I am red and the ball I am holding is my partner in various activities including crime, Arc are looking for a man with a beard, and a teen and-&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;quot;Found them.&amp;quot; Arc says quietly and sure enough there they were in front of me with the keeper explaining to them.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;quot;So I am dead.&amp;quot; The teen say.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;quot;I believe so, I can give you the knowledge you need to use the powers you were given if you want.&amp;quot; says the old man.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;quot;Sure.&amp;quot; The teen says. &amp;quot;Ah, I see now thank you.&amp;quot;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;quot;You are welcome and it seems our friends is here as well.&amp;quot; the keeper says turning to me and Arc.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;quot;Red, 2, this young man is named Coldplay and the lady besides him is Olympia.&amp;quot; the old man continues.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;quot;Let me get this straight we were killed and these two are friends with the guy who brought us back.&amp;quot; Olympia says.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;quot;Correct.&amp;quot; Arc says.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;quot;I think something is coming.&amp;quot; Coldplay says look as a bush.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;quot;Hello, I am that friend.&amp;quot; Boss says coming out of the bush. &amp;quot;Anyway I suggest you run as that thing is stronger when people desire to cause others pain.&amp;quot;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;With that the keeper vanished behind him is a demon born from war. We ran as fast as we could. Until I sprayed it with Bromomethyl ethyl ketone.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Coldplay is recovering from the chase. &amp;quot;Your friend is insane.&amp;quot;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;quot;I mean boss isn&#039;t crazy, he is just an idiot trying to create a story to represent thousands of unique anomalies, researchers, businesses, and other stories but refuses to write overly meta comedies with some action scenes and fights.&amp;quot; I retort.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;quot;I see.&amp;quot; Olympia says.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;quot;And he sucks at writing.&amp;quot; Arc says.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;quot;That is just rude.&amp;quot; the book keeper says from behind me.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;quot;Hi, Book keeper.&amp;quot; Olympia says unsurprised.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;quot;Hello.&amp;quot; The keeper says. &amp;quot;You see the reason he made the monster chase you was to show you this.&amp;quot;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The keeper points behind himself and sure enough a building this is unmistakably a foundation site. The five of us move towards the building.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;quot;What is boss up to.&amp;quot; I say.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;quot;I don&#039;t know, 1.&amp;quot; Arc said as we reach the entrance.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;After Coldplay melted the door we went in the site and have Olympia walked us around the site along the way I picked up my favorite weapon just in case, a &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.scpwiki.com/scp-2818&quot;&gt;Barrett M82A1&lt;/a&gt;. When we finished the tour we went back to the break room.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;quot;This was interesting but usually I am ventriloquizing bad jokes to make tomatoes destroy murderous teddy bears or something crazy like that.&amp;quot; I say drinking coffee.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;quot;We will get to that part in a minute.&amp;quot; A voice says.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;quot;Yay unknown voice is saying ominous stuff.&amp;quot; Arc says sarcastically before the group vanishes from the room.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Red wakes up in a strange room, sighing he transforms his skeleton into the same material as bladewood petals and activates bone armour. Getting up he think about the last time he used it, running at least a hundred miles wait the foundation uses kilometers not that it matters in this case, tearing apart a moose man that destroyed a city, took hits from that kaiju, and since I weigh 310.5 kilograms in this state I feel sorry for anyone hit with my gun. The wall was surprisingly fragile it only took one punch. Walking out of the room I see what the voice meant there is a broken down tank.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;quot;Every broken down tank I encountered has a kill count and are indestructible, so this can&#039;t end well.&amp;quot; I complain.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;immediately after I said the tank shot a harpoon at me and it missed. This is embarrassing. After it missed I walked up and flipped it.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;quot;Dang it.&amp;quot; the Voice says. &amp;quot;Umm, go skeleton that very conveniently burns at the minimum temperature required to mold your bones.&amp;quot;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;quot;That is honestly the most threatening thing I heard in years.&amp;quot; I say before getting punched in the face by a burning skeleton.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;My skull and bone armour fused together, I can&#039;t hear or see. I throw my rifle away from were I think the monster is before getting bear hugged. It hurts a lot I am being cooked alive, in fact my blood is evaporating and my bone armour is air tight. I am going to explode.&lt;br /&gt;
&amp;#8212;-&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;My name is Arthur and I am the god of this world. Only two can stand against me, two ideas that refuse to die. They have no power to oppose me but, they slip into my other ideas. I feel I should hate them but I can&#039;t. And right now I just had a burning skeleton blow one up. Their blood now a mist, organs scattered and shriveled, skin melt and metal shell broken. They aren&#039;t dead and you aren&#039;t here for gore. A few cell live and start to reproduce. In less than a minute the cells became lizard men and bovine hearts, the skeleton didn&#039;t stand a chance, the idea it fought was cunning and while the idea fears the frost and flames, Walter isn&#039;t allowed to lose with out my permission. The skeleton&#039;s bones were broken and flame extinguished. Walter, the idea that I can&#039;t kill, picks up his gun and leads his lizard and bovine children onwards.&lt;br /&gt;
&amp;#8212;-&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It seems it&#039;s my turn to be the narrator, yay.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;quot;I mean to be rude, where the fuck am I?&amp;quot; I yell.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;quot;Please don&#039;t curse, orb.&amp;quot; Says the voice.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;quot;Ok, so now you are you revealing yourself dumbass.&amp;quot; I say.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;quot;Okay, I just released the other Walter in the room and your Walter is a couple minutes away.&amp;quot; Dumbass says.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A rabbit hops towards me which I manifest a block above and crush it.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;quot;Damn it.&amp;quot; dumbass yells.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;quot;What is your problem, dumbass.&amp;quot; I say.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;quot;This scene was met to show your capabilities, your care for Walter, and helplessness without without him. While being funny in that you panic in an attempt to slow down the rabbit before getting saved Walter.&amp;quot; The dumbass explains.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;quot;All my abilities are clearly listed on my part of the description and why do you need that?&amp;quot; I ask.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;quot;Sh, Walter is almost here.&amp;quot; The voice say.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;About a minute goes by before a wall explodes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;quot;Hi Arc.&amp;quot; 1 says.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;quot;Hi, 1.&amp;quot; I say as the bullet that caused the explosion transforms into a weaver. &amp;quot;By the way what are your current modifications and army.&amp;quot;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;quot;I have the Peripheral Jumper&#039;s special sensory organ and Gaia enhanced bladewood bone armour. The army consists of 5 lizard kings, 2 dark hearts, 500 illusory butterflies, 10 giant wasp, 4 ice spiders, 7 ufos, a blood wolf, and that weaver.&amp;quot; 1 lists.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To be continued.(maybe, I would need this book back)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;State of anomalies effected:&lt;/strong&gt; Olympia and SCP-547-D both returned as they were before the event and are therefore deceased. SCP-1230-1 behaves the same as previously and doesn&#039;t acknowledge questions about it.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div id=&quot;wiki-tab-0-1&quot; style=&quot;display:none&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Item #:&lt;/strong&gt; SCP-5547&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Clearance:&lt;/strong&gt; 3&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;container-class:&lt;/strong&gt; thaumiel&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;disruption-class:&lt;/strong&gt; ekhi&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;risk-class:&lt;/strong&gt; notice&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;threat level:&lt;/strong&gt; red&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Special Containment Procedures:&lt;/strong&gt; SCP-5547-1, SCP-5547-2, and SCP-5547-3 are held in a 10x10x5 meter containment cell connect to 2 (two) standard humanoid containment chambers. Should any instance of SCP-5547 misbehave, threaten SCP-5547-1 with thermal weaponry until they stop. When a discussion event occurs attempts to convince them to bring things back with them or take things can be done with the approval of an O5, such attempts are to stop if SCP-5547-3 claims &amp;quot;They won&#039;t like that&amp;quot;. SCP-5547-1 and 2 are to hand over any item it brings back but may request them for future narrative events. After a narrative event a d-class is to be sent in to retrieve the SCP-5547-4 instance, which will then be added to the site breakroom. Should a death event occur the room is to be sealed for one hour. SCP-5547-5A is to be managed by Director Smith, who is to keep in contact thru SCP-5547-5B which kept in the middle of SCP-5547&#039;s containment cell.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Description:&lt;/strong&gt; SCP-5547-1 is a red type capable of altering it&#039;s biology to a high degree showing the ability to replicate traits of several anomalous lifeforms. It primarily takes the form of an underweight Caucasian male teenager and in this form displays sapience and sentience. SCP-5547-1 displays extreme thermophobia do to thermal weaponry causing several death events. Death events are the events that occur when SCP-5547-1 dies. Five minutes after it&#039;s death a gaseous substance will fly out of SCP-5547-2 and start releasing a unknown amount of energy for approximately 40 minutes resulting in an instance of SCP-5547-1 with all memories of the previous instance. During discussion events they spend most of their time listening, making simple suggestions to SCP-5547-3. During narrative events they have shown anomalous knowledge, however they have not been confirmed to use this knowledge outside of them. SCP-5547-1 is generally friendly and talkative, often talking to SCP-5547-2 or asking SCP-5547-3 for snacks and to help in clean the containment chamber.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;SCP-5547-2 is a light blue crystal ball with a radius of 30&amp;#160;cm and a mass of 50 kilograms that constantly produces EVE, SCP-5547-2 is at least as intelligent as an adolescent human but do to it&#039;s aggressive behaviour this can&#039;t be can&#039;t test further. SCP-5547-2 is made of a substance that is indestructible, non conductive, and completely unreactive. SCP-5547-2 can manifest SCP-5547-2A which is theorized to be made of the same substance as SCP-5547-2 within 10 meters of it and stay in the same position relative to it. It can move SCP-5547-2A with it&#039;s thoughts however the substance will disappear if farther than 10 meters from SCP-5547-2 and can&#039;t directly interact with SCP-5547-2. It uses SCP-5547-2A to attack anyone near it other than SCP-5547-1 or 3. During discussion events it is very critical while offering little advice. The object is sarcastic, and openly hostile towards everyone except SCP-5547-1. In narrative events it shown high levels of thaumatology capabilities in SCP-5547-1&#039;s possession.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;SCP-5547-3 is a underweight Caucasian male teenager with the ability to alter reality with a method unknown to the foundation to an unknown degree. During discussion events it will usually suggest a human or humanoid with knowledge of the anomalous, and two anomalies which it comes up with ideas for stories including them and SCP-5547-1 and 2. During narrative events he stays in the real world and handles the side effects of narrative events, only appearing in narratives if something goes wrong in it.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Discussion events normally occur a week before a narrative event, however they have also lead to the disappearance, changes, destruction, and appearance of anomalies and people with knowledge of the anomalous. SCP-5547-3 always starts the conversation, SCP-5547-1 listens quietly to him, and SCP-5547-2 points out lack of originality, inconsistencies and missing information. For an example of a discussion event see addendum 1.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Narrative events consists of the disappearance of SCP-5547-1 and 2, the humanoid mentioned, and depending on unknown variables instances of the anomalies mentioned. SCP-5547-3 will then use it&#039;s reality altering abilities to act in place of the humanoid, and depending on the anomaly act in it&#039;s place, explain to those associated with the anomaly it is safe, or nothing. After a time varying from 5 minutes to 6 months SCP-5547-1 and 2 return in the containment cell, unless a death event occurs in during the narrative event then only SCP-5547-2 returns. The Humanoid returns as it was either before or at the end of the narrative sapience beings claim they got to choose, however they keep memory of the event either way, if the humanoid is not sapience it is always returned to how it was before the event with no memory of it reappearing where SCP-5547-3 claims they belong. Anomalies that are not in SCP-5547-1 or 2&#039;s possession or destroy return to where SCP-5547-3 claims they belong, anomalies destroyed don&#039;t reappear, anomalies in SCP-5547-1 or 2&#039;s possession at the end of the evw return in SCP-5547-1 or 2&#039;s possession. On the desk in one of the standard humanoid containment chamber connected their containment chamber SCP-5547-4 will appear. SCP-5547-4 are books written in English about the items that disappeared in the recent narrative event. SCP-5547-4 instances have no anomalous properties other than their origin. For an example of a narrative event see addendum 2.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;SCP-5547-5A is site-42 which resides in the lower narrative &amp;quot;New Beginning&amp;quot;. Site-42 has copies of various anomalies that are free to roam sites, a construction staff that always has the exact building materials they need, an infinite amount of d-class and working copies of various anomalous tools and weapons. All non d-class Foundation personal have been unable to be harmed when in the site. SCP-5547-5B is a device that allows for communication between site-42 and the main reality as well as transfer between the two.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Addendum 1:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;blockquote&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;SCP-5547-1:&lt;/strong&gt; Do we reintroduce ourselves, boss.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;SCP-5547-2:&lt;/strong&gt; Well, I am deintroducing myself, hi my name is [[REDACTED]].&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;SCP-5547-3:&lt;/strong&gt; This is a discussion event anyway we are likely done with &amp;quot;new beginning&amp;quot; so here is the ne-&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;SCP-5547-1:&lt;/strong&gt; I have a suggestion.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;SCP-5547-2:&lt;/strong&gt; It is probably better than dumbass&#039;s idea.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;SCP-5547-3:&lt;/strong&gt; Orb is probably right.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;SCP-5547-1:&lt;/strong&gt; I think we should give site-42 to the foundation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;SCP-5547-3:&lt;/strong&gt; Why?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;SCP-5547-1:&lt;/strong&gt; You like happy endings, the foundation doesn&#039;t have a happy story not that it is ending soon, that site is meant to hold the keys to success, which you had to make in a lower narrative because we are stuck in your head and a Mary sue site would get downvoted into oblivion near instantly also you just thought of it but can&#039;t say that your self.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;SCP-5547-2:&lt;/strong&gt; 1 has a point.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;SCP-5547-3:&lt;/strong&gt; I might as well get rid of the antimeme then as they are going to go with this no matter what. They, the readers are going to mad I didn&#039;t show them the rest of new beginnings&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;SCP-5547-2:&lt;/strong&gt; Dumbass, I might have a secondary role of being a somewhat abstract embodiment of your doubt, but your fear of the readers is getting ridiculous, especially since you expect the meta behavior of the article to protect your weird description and containment procedures.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;SCP-5547-3:&lt;/strong&gt; Let&#039;s do this thing.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;lt;End of discussion event&amp;gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Addendum 2:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Humanoid effected:&lt;/strong&gt; Dr. Smith&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Anomalies effected:&lt;/strong&gt; SCP-547-D and Olympia&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Lasted for:&lt;/strong&gt; On going&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;SCP-5547-3 Behavior changes:&lt;/strong&gt; Started to make SCP-5547-5B.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;SCP-5547-4 instance:&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;strong&gt;New Beginning chapter 50: To be continued&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;blockquote&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;quot;Where am I?&amp;quot; Dr. Smith says after appearing.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;quot;Site-42 the answer to keters, the narratives, and anomalies.&amp;quot; I respond.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;quot;1 is over exaggerating but we think it will be useful for your future endeavors.&amp;quot; Arc says.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;quot;What are you guys?&amp;quot; Dr. Smith.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;quot;Did you not read the article after we mentioned there being antimemes removed from it, you are a terrible head researcher?&amp;quot; Arc says.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;quot;I mean the information in the article mentioned isn&#039;t entirely correct for about the boss, he isn&#039;t a horror writer he is not even acknowledged as a writer on the site yet.&amp;quot; I start explaining. &amp;quot;You see before this idea came to be he posted 6 ideas a color changing mantis shrimp, spork workers, a teenager with an accelerated cell cycle, a sentient crystal ball that evolved into Arc, a dande lion, and straight up the tarrasque and dnd player characters and logic items over the six versions. All these ideas fell flat but 2 didn&#039;t die I already revealed one but the other was the the teen how is now the handsome fellow standing in front of you.&amp;quot;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;quot;Ok.&amp;quot; My head researcher says following along.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;quot;Dumbass realized he couldn&#039;t drop us so he put us together the first idea after we met was an explanation of how SCP-2000 and the title of administer work with us restoring the planet and foundation.&amp;quot; Arc continues. &amp;quot;But it wasn&#039;t enjoyable so now we are here.&amp;quot;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;quot;Sorry to interrupt.&amp;quot; Boss says appearing. &amp;quot;The device is done shall we take our leave?&amp;quot;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;quot;Sure.&amp;quot; I say. &amp;quot;Site director Smith you know what to do, the rest of the staff should arrive soon, oh and please keep an eye on Olympia and Coldplay.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;And with that SCP-5547-1, 2, and 3 appeared back in the real world.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;footer-wikiwalk-nav&quot;&gt;
