&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Description:&lt;/strong&gt; One VISUS brand 3&amp;#160;1/4&amp;quot; floppy disk, in poor condition due to inferior late-model materials. The disk contains a small portion of a previously-unknown early build of Portico 1.0, the operating system coded by software pioneer Mark Post which made his company a household name.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Notes:&lt;/strong&gt; After Post&#039;s death, the disk was discovered by his biographer who sold it to a reporter for the &lt;em&gt;New York Times.&lt;/em&gt; Software analysis revealed that the code still contained comments from software engineers at Ananasoft Inc., indicating that it was actually plagiarized from the competing ANANASYS Cayenne operating system. Post was subsequently excised from his company&#039;s promotional material.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
&lt;td style=&quot;border: 1px solid black; padding-right: 12px; padding-top: 12px; padding-bottom: 12px; padding-left: 24px;background-color: #F3F3F3&quot; colspan=&quot;2&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;So, what makes these things appear? Because they don&#039;t &lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;always&lt;/span&gt; appear. I&#039;d like to get as many Sections looking at this as possible.&lt;/em&gt; [Blank, Dr. H.]&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
